      "raw_text": "An order was adopted by the city\ncouncil last night cutting out auto\nmatte sprinklers and making it\ncompulsory during sprinkling hours\nto hold the nozzle in the hand. This\naction was taken through a resolu.\nton introduced in the city council\nby r. l.. Dalke.\n\n\nWater and the relief of the water\nfamine occupied a good portion of\nthe time of the city council last\nnight. A delegation of women from\nthe lower portion of Lidgerwood\nwhich had been turned down in its\ncall on Mayor Pratt, visited the\ncity council. Mrs. A. c. Toms was\nthe spokesman and painted a vivid\npicture Of what the people in her\nlocality have put up with recently\n\n\nCouncilmen said that they had\ndone everything possible in the way"
